    <entry>
        <title type="html"><![CDATA[Gradle and Palantir Docker Plugin]]></title>
        <id>https://grauds.github.io/clematis.doc/blog/gradle-update-post</id>
        <link href="https://grauds.github.io/clematis.doc/blog/gradle-update-post"/>
        <updated>2025-05-24T00:00:00.000Z</updated>
        <summary type="html"><![CDATA[The Palantir Docker Plugin is now EOL, which probably is the old news,]]></summary>
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>The <a href="https://github.com/palantir/gradle-docker" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Palantir Docker Plugin</a> is now EOL, which probably is the old news,
however, the worse part is that it is waiting to be updated for Gradle 8.12 and up:
<a href="https://github.com/palantir/gradle-docker/issues/801" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://github.com/palantir/gradle-docker/issues/801</a>.</p>
<p>Some Clematis APIs are dependent on the plugin, so looking for workarounds or removal.</p>]]></content>
